main event: Three bright, round, luminous objects were sighted in the northeast sky by Captain _____ near Kingsville, Maryland, on 25 February 1953.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be self-illuminated and about forty degrees above the horizon., The objects initially seemed stationary and then moved in a circular trajectory., One object dimmed and brightened alternately at intervals of about one second., Observations lasted for about five minutes before the objects disappeared behind clouds., The report includes qualifications of the observer, detailing his background in physics and aerial observations.
witness description: Captain, Medical Service Corps, Chief of Radiological Hygiene Division, Army Chemical Center.
